1
00:00:06,204 --> 00:00:07,705
MIDGE: Ugh, I'm so late.
They're gonna kill me.

2
00:00:07,789 --> 00:00:09,499
ROSE: I'm late, too. My class is at 8:00.

3
00:00:09,583 --> 00:00:10,834
MIDGE: I'm late for work!

4
00:00:10,918 --> 00:00:12,126
ROSE: That makes you more important?

5
00:00:12,210 --> 00:00:13,712
ABE: My fancy socks are missing.

6
00:00:13,796 --> 00:00:15,339
Hey, is Zelda here yet?

7
00:00:15,423 --> 00:00:17,132
Which ones are your fancy socks?

8
00:00:17,216 --> 00:00:19,051
-I only have one pair of fancy socks.
-MIDGE: They're the ones

9
00:00:19,135 --> 00:00:21,178
with the floating
martini glasses on them.

10
00:00:21,262 --> 00:00:22,972
Those are my comical socks!

11
00:00:23,056 --> 00:00:24,473
Why do you have comical socks?

12
00:00:24,557 --> 00:00:26,016
Are you talking about the
ones with pineapples on them?

13
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,309
Those are comical socks, too.

14
00:00:27,393 --> 00:00:30,145
Why do you have two
pairs of comical socks?

15
00:00:30,229 --> 00:00:31,647
Abe, you're dressed.
Why are you asking about socks?

16
00:00:31,731 --> 00:00:33,941
Because I'm dressed for the university.

17
00:00:34,025 --> 00:00:37,486
I go to Bell Labs later and
they dress more eclectic.

18
00:00:37,570 --> 00:00:40,197
Sounds like a job for
pineapple socks to me.

19
00:00:40,281 --> 00:00:42,951
I'll just bring a pair of fun,
weekend slacks for Bell Labs

20
00:00:43,035 --> 00:00:44,369
and change in the taxi.

21
00:00:44,453 --> 00:00:45,996
BOTH: Do not change in the taxi.

22
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:47,664
I don't have time to change at school.

23
00:00:47,748 --> 00:00:49,833
BOTH: Do not change in the taxi.

24
00:00:49,917 --> 00:00:51,501
-CHILD: Mama!
-Coming!

25
00:00:51,585 --> 00:00:53,128
ROSE: Why do you have comical socks?

26
00:00:53,212 --> 00:00:55,213
-Did you call me?
-No.

27
00:00:55,297 --> 00:00:56,548
Could've sworn you called me.

28
00:00:56,632 --> 00:00:59,009
It's Zelda's day off, by the way.

29
00:00:59,093 --> 00:01:00,427
No one told me.

30
00:01:00,511 --> 00:01:01,887
I told you multiple times.

31
00:01:01,971 --> 00:01:03,346
She was supposed to watch the kids.

32
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:04,723
Get their father to watch them.

33
00:01:04,807 --> 00:01:06,057
That's who should watch them.

34
00:01:06,141 --> 00:01:07,768
Tomorrow is Joel's day to watch them.

35
00:01:07,852 --> 00:01:10,021
If you want to make a
change, give Joel a call.

36
00:01:10,105 --> 00:01:11,147
I am not calling Joel.

37
00:01:11,231 --> 00:01:13,733
There is no food and
I'm literally starving.

38
00:01:13,817 --> 00:01:15,568
You are not "literally starving."

39
00:01:15,652 --> 00:01:16,986
-CHILD: Mama!
-Coming!

40
00:01:17,070 --> 00:01:18,237
ABE: I guess I don't
get to use the bathroom.

41
00:01:18,321 --> 00:01:19,697
ROSE: Like I'm stopping you.

42
00:01:19,781 --> 00:01:22,199
Now, that time you called me.

43
00:01:22,283 --> 00:01:24,201
If it wasn't you, who was it?

44
00:01:24,285 --> 00:01:26,203
-Esther.
-Esther?

45
00:01:26,287 --> 00:01:28,205
Really?

46
00:01:28,289 --> 00:01:30,833
Hey! Hey, hey!

47
00:01:30,917 --> 00:01:32,209
Esther said a word!

48
00:01:32,293 --> 00:01:34,755
-She said a word?
-Good for her.

49
00:01:34,839 --> 00:01:36,423
Should we take a cab?

50
00:01:36,507 --> 00:01:37,966
No, walking's faster.

51
00:01:38,050 --> 00:01:39,384
When you're not in heels.

52
00:01:39,468 --> 00:01:41,678
-And you are not starving.
-I am, too.

53
00:01:41,762 --> 00:01:43,722
Then your muscle and
tissue would be breaking down.

54
00:01:43,806 --> 00:01:45,223
Your abdomen would be distended.

55
00:01:45,307 --> 00:01:47,267
-Your menstruation would cease.
-Abe, stop.

56
00:01:47,351 --> 00:01:49,394
-What is that?
-She said she was literally starving.

57
00:01:49,478 --> 00:01:50,896
There is no food

58
00:01:50,980 --> 00:01:52,356
and I am literally,
figuratively starving.

59
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:53,690
-I got to go!
-Me, too.

60
00:01:53,774 --> 00:01:55,943
What have I been saying?

61
00:01:57,945 --> 00:01:59,905
-Someone's got to stay.
-I can't stay.

62
00:01:59,989 --> 00:02:01,407
-None of us can stay.
-ESTHER: Mama.

63
00:02:01,491 --> 00:02:03,242
Call Mrs. Fulber, tell
her it's an emergency.

64
00:02:03,326 --> 00:02:04,567
-ROSE: This isn't an emergency.
-MIDGE: It kind of is.

65
00:02:04,651 --> 00:02:05,036
Mama.

66
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,871
ABE: Now I'm
second-guessing these slacks.

67
00:02:06,955 --> 00:02:08,539
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

68
00:02:08,623 --> 00:02:10,166
B. Altman, where may I direct your call?

69
00:02:10,250 --> 00:02:11,668
I will connect you.

70
00:02:11,752 --> 00:02:13,628
B. Altman, where may I direct your call?
I will connect you.

71
00:02:13,712 --> 00:02:15,421
B. Altman, where may I direct your call?

72
